1
00:01:14,239 --> 00:01:14,959
Tang Yi.

2
00:01:15,879 --> 00:01:16,640
I'm here for this.

3
00:01:18,079 --> 00:01:19,439
This is hilarious.

4
00:01:33,120 --> 00:01:34,359
The wind is so strong.

5
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:37,280
You okay?

6
00:01:37,359 --> 00:01:38,079
I'm fine, I'm fine.

7
00:01:38,359 --> 00:01:39,439
Quick, catch it! Hurry!

8
00:01:58,920 --> 00:02:00,159
Come on, quit faking it.

9
00:02:00,439 --> 00:02:01,239
Are you even a man?

10
00:02:01,359 --> 00:02:02,280
You can't even catch this ball.

11
00:02:02,400 --> 00:02:03,640
Qiyue, I can't do this anymore.

12
00:02:03,719 --> 00:02:04,760
I really can't go on.

13
00:02:04,879 --> 00:02:05,920
Just give me a break.

14
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:07,719
Let's just admit defeat this once.

15
00:02:07,760 --> 00:02:08,639
No way.

16
00:02:09,120 --> 00:02:10,520
In Qiao Qiyue's dictionary,

17
00:02:10,759 --> 00:02:12,360
the word "lose" doesn't exist.

18
00:02:13,360 --> 00:02:15,039
Director Zeng finally showed some mercy

19
00:02:15,159 --> 00:02:16,199
and let us have a team building event.

20
00:02:16,319 --> 00:02:18,639
Why go so hard, my lady?

21
00:02:18,919 --> 00:02:19,560
Get up.

22
00:02:21,360 --> 00:02:21,960
Hurry up.

23
00:02:24,039 --> 00:02:24,560
Pass the ball.

24
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:25,800
Get ready, get ready.

25
00:02:42,599 --> 00:02:43,560
Why is she here?

26
00:02:43,680 --> 00:02:44,479
I have no idea.

27
00:02:44,879 --> 00:02:46,080
Isn't this a team building event?

28
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:48,120
What? Am I not welcome to join?

29
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:50,800
You guys carry on. We're leaving.

30
00:03:03,120 --> 00:03:04,000
Pei Xi, come here.

31
00:03:11,840 --> 00:03:12,639
Don't be mad.

32
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:13,360
Come on, have a drink.

33
00:03:13,560 --> 00:03:14,479
Here, cool down.

34
00:03:17,879 --> 00:03:18,879
What are you all staring at?

35
00:03:19,039 --> 00:03:19,719
What are you looking at?

36
00:03:20,280 --> 00:03:21,240
I'm sorry, Qiyue.

37
00:03:21,319 --> 00:03:21,879
We're not looking anymore.

38
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:22,879
Come on, cheers, cheers!

39
00:03:25,199 --> 00:03:26,039
Daniel.

40
00:03:35,960 --> 00:03:36,719
Looks like...

41
00:03:36,879 --> 00:03:38,719
there's something Dr. Jiang isn't good at after all.

42
00:04:03,479 --> 00:04:04,120
You okay?

43
00:04:05,039 --> 00:04:05,599
Nice one!

44
00:04:11,639 --> 00:04:12,280
You alright?

45
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:13,159
I'm fine.

46
00:04:15,439 --> 00:04:16,360
That was just a slip.

47
00:04:16,639 --> 00:04:17,399
Let's go again.

48
00:04:19,680 --> 00:04:20,519
You up for this or not?

49
00:04:20,839 --> 00:04:21,560
Again.

50
00:04:27,120 --> 00:04:27,680
This...

51
00:04:27,959 --> 00:04:29,120
Are they going to fight? It's so intense.

52
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:30,079
One more time.

53
00:04:30,560 --> 00:04:31,240
Come on.

54
00:04:41,040 --> 00:04:42,160
You two.

55
00:05:07,120 --> 00:05:08,000
Just stay put.

56
00:05:08,639 --> 00:05:09,519
What a perfect opportunity.

57
00:05:09,920 --> 00:05:11,759
Plenty of people will be fussing over her soon.

58
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:12,600
Sit down.

59
00:05:16,560 --> 00:05:17,279
You okay?

60
00:05:17,360 --> 00:05:18,040
I'm fine.

61
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:21,759
Are you alright?

62
00:05:23,040 --> 00:05:24,439
I'm fine, keep going.

63
00:05:27,519 --> 00:05:28,199
She twisted her ankle.

64
00:05:29,879 --> 00:05:31,920
It's fine, I'll just rest over there.

65
00:05:32,680 --> 00:05:33,560
Let me help you over.

66
00:05:40,079 --> 00:05:40,759
Come on.

67
00:05:42,959 --> 00:05:43,759
Careful.

68
00:05:54,319 --> 00:05:55,040
Does it hurt here?

69
00:05:56,879 --> 00:05:57,560
What about here?

70
00:05:59,879 --> 00:06:00,759
Here?

71
00:06:02,560 --> 00:06:04,000
It's swelling. I'll get the first-aid kit.

72
00:06:04,240 --> 00:06:04,759
Wait a second.

73
00:06:04,959 --> 00:06:05,759
I'm fine.

74
00:06:28,079 --> 00:06:29,000
Thanks, thank you, boss.

75
00:06:39,680 --> 00:06:40,240
Here.

76
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:44,839
Take it easy. Don't overdo it again.

77
00:06:48,279 --> 00:06:49,120
I know.

78
00:06:50,079 --> 00:06:51,120
I was parachuted in here.

79
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:53,399
None of you like me.

80
00:06:54,240 --> 00:06:55,199
But it's okay.

81
00:06:55,879 --> 00:06:56,800
I don't mind.

82
00:06:57,600 --> 00:06:58,240
Really.

83
00:06:59,040 --> 00:06:59,959
On the contrary,

84
00:07:00,279 --> 00:07:02,839
I'm especially happy today.

85
00:07:03,839 --> 00:07:04,680
Because

86
00:07:05,839 --> 00:07:07,519
today marks the day Daniel and I

87
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:12,079
have known each other for 5,475 days.

88
00:07:13,839 --> 00:07:16,319
5,475 days.

89
00:07:16,800 --> 00:07:18,319
A whole 15 years!

90
00:07:19,399 --> 00:07:20,480
Tell me,

91
00:07:21,120 --> 00:07:23,439
how many 15-year stretches do we get in life?

92
00:07:32,439 --> 00:07:33,240
Daniel,

93
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:35,720
this drink is for you.

94
00:07:36,800 --> 00:07:37,639
Thank you

95
00:07:38,199 --> 00:07:39,399
for giving Lin Fei'er

96
00:07:39,639 --> 00:07:41,920
the best years of her life.

97
00:07:54,639 --> 00:07:56,120
You've had too much. Stop drinking.

98
00:07:59,519 --> 00:08:01,600
I knew you still cared about me.

99
00:08:03,399 --> 00:08:04,319
You, my dear,

100
00:08:05,040 --> 00:08:05,959
just won't admit it.

101
00:08:16,879 --> 00:08:17,800
Dr. Tang,

102
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:20,079
this drink is for you.

103
00:08:20,519 --> 00:08:21,759
That case with Zhao Mumu,

104
00:08:22,199 --> 00:08:23,759
you really opened my eyes.

105
00:08:24,160 --> 00:08:24,879
I'll down mine.

106
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:26,040
Drink as you please.

107
00:08:44,399 --> 00:08:45,200
I'll drink it for her.

108
00:08:51,799 --> 00:08:52,919
We... we're full.

109
00:08:53,120 --> 00:08:54,000
We'll get going first.

110
00:08:54,159 --> 00:08:55,159
You all keep eating. Yes, yes.

111
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:56,679
Enjoy your meal. Bye.

112
00:08:56,799 --> 00:08:57,519
Qiao Qiyue.

113
00:08:58,519 --> 00:08:59,279
Come back.

114
00:09:11,399 --> 00:09:13,080
Since Dr. Lin is being so sincere,

115
00:09:13,600 --> 00:09:15,039
I'll drink this glass myself.

116
00:09:19,240 --> 00:09:20,080
This glass,

117
00:09:21,399 --> 00:09:22,759
I toast to Qiyue and Pei Xi.

118
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:26,279
If it weren't for you two,

119
00:09:26,519 --> 00:09:28,080
the surgery wouldn't have gone so smoothly.

120
00:09:28,720 --> 00:09:29,360
Cheers.

121
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:30,679
Forget it.

122
00:09:30,759 --> 00:09:31,799
You can't handle alcohol, so don't drink.

123
00:09:44,720 --> 00:09:45,679
This glass,

124
00:09:46,840 --> 00:09:47,840
I toast to my Senior brother.

125
00:09:48,519 --> 00:09:50,480
Thank you for taking care of me all these years.

126
00:09:51,120 --> 00:09:51,759
If it weren't for you,

127
00:09:51,840 --> 00:09:53,720
I might not have made it this far so smoothly.

128
00:09:58,919 --> 00:09:59,960
If you don't mind,

129
00:10:00,120 --> 00:10:02,440
I'll always be your closest junior sister.

130
00:10:19,879 --> 00:10:20,679
With this toast,

131
00:10:23,960 --> 00:10:25,480
I sincerely hope you both

132
00:10:26,039 --> 00:10:28,120
clear up the misunderstanding soon

133
00:10:30,559 --> 00:10:31,600
and Reconcile.

134
00:11:00,039 --> 00:11:00,639
Let's go.

135
00:11:32,799 --> 00:11:34,279
Brushing your teeth right after eating sweets,

136
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:36,200
does that really prevent cavities?

137
00:11:36,639 --> 00:11:37,519
Of course not.

138
00:11:37,799 --> 00:11:39,679
Our mouths contain many bacteria.

139
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:41,080
They break down sugars

140
00:11:41,360 --> 00:11:43,600
and produce large amounts of acidic substances,

141
00:11:43,840 --> 00:11:45,039
causing the tooth crown to soften.

142
00:11:45,279 --> 00:11:47,519
If we brush our teeth right at that moment,

143
00:11:47,639 --> 00:11:49,519
it actually damages the teeth.

144
00:11:49,720 --> 00:11:51,440
So after eating sweets,

145
00:11:51,559 --> 00:11:52,360
be sure to remember

146
00:11:52,440 --> 00:11:54,639
to give your teeth half an hour to recover,

147
00:11:54,759 --> 00:11:56,000
and then brush gently.
